Visit the eBay Motors website featured in the Sources section of this article, then click on "Sign in" at the top of the screen. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/23/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Enter your eBay User ID and password, then click on "Sign in." If you are new to eBay, click on "Register," then follow the prompts to create an account. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/55/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on "Parts and Accessories" from the category list to indicate you are selling an auto part. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f3/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f3/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on the automobile type of the auto part you are selling. You will be able to choose from categories such as boats, trailers, motorcycles, cars, and more. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8c/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/8c/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select the type of auto part you are selling. For example, if you chose "Car and Truck parts" as your automobile type, you can indicate your auto part as being an engine, filter, glass fixture, and more. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/1f/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select the name of the auto part you are selling. For example, if you are selling interior car parts, you can choose from options such as glove box, cup holder, sun visor, and more. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d0/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d0/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on "Save and Continue" to save the product details of your auto part. You will then be taken to the Parts Compatibility tool. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/22/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet5.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/22/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet5.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-6Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Using the Parts Compatibility tool may help maximize the exposure of your listing by displaying it to buyers looking for a specific auto part compatible with their automobile. Click on "Search Catalog," then enter the name of the part manufacturer or complete the fields that indicate the year, make, and model of the automobile that the part belongs to. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b2/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Browse through the search results and choose "Select" when you find your auto part. If you cannot find your auto part using the Parts Compatibility tool, you can enter your details manually by clicking on "Specify Part Compatibility. "{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/25/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/25/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on "Confirm Parts Details" to add the product details for your auto part to your listing. A table that indicates all compatible vehicles that can use the auto part will also be included in your listing. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5f/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/5f/Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/aid1682279-v4-728px-Sell-Auto-Parts-on-eBay-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"529","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
